Appraise Magic Value			TYPE:General			VISIBLE:YES																																																					PRESKILL:3,Appraise=5,Knowledge (Arcana)=5,Spellcraft=5																			DESC:Your ability to determine an item's worth and your knowledge of magic allow you to determine the exact properties of a magic item without the use of the identify spell or similar magic.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.103	BENEFIT:If you know that an item is magical, you can use the Appraise skill to identify the item's properties.
Ascetic Hunter				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FavoredEnemy														PREFEAT:1,Improved Unarmed Strike																																																				DESC:You have gone beyond the bounds of your monastic training to incorporate new modes of bringing the unlawful to justice.																																																																																																																																																																																																																	BONUS:UDAM|CLASS.Monk|("CL=Ranger")																														SOURCEPAGE:p.105	BENEFIT:When you use an unarmed strike to deliver a stunning attack against a favored enemy, you can add one-half your favored enemy bonus on damage rolls to the DC of your stunning attempt.
Ascetic Knight				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Smite Evil															PREFEAT:1,Improved Unarmed Strike																																																				DESC:You have blended your training as a paladin and as a monk into one seamless whole.																																																																																																																																																																																																																							BONUS:UDAM|CLASS.Monk|("CL=Paladin")	BONUS:VAR|SmiteEvilDamageLvl|("CL=Monk")																						SOURCEPAGE:p.105	BENEFIT:Your paladin and monk levels stack for the purpose of determining your unarmed strike damage. For example, a human 3rd-level paladin/1st-level monk would deal 1d8 points of damage with her unarmed strike. Your paladin and monk levels also stack when determining the extra damage dealt by your smite evil ability.
Ascetic Mage				TYPE:General																												PREFEAT:1,Improved Unarmed Strike																																		PRESPELLCAST:MEMORIZE=N	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=2											DESC:You practice an unusual martial art that mixes self-taught spellcasting and melee attacks to great effect.																																																																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:VAR|MonkAC|max(0,CHA)-max(0,WIS)	BONUS:VAR|MonkAC|("CL=Sorcerer")																SOURCEPAGE:p.105	BENEFIT:As a swift action that doesn't provoke attacks of opportunity, you can sacrifice one of your daily allotment of spells to add a bonus to your unarmed strike attack rolls and damage rolls for 1 round. The bonus is equal to the level of the spell sacrificed. The spell is lost as if you had cast it. If you have levels in sorcerer and monk, those levels stack for the purpose of determining your AC bonus.
Ascetic Rogue				TYPE:General																												PREFEAT:1,Improved Unarmed Strike									PREMULT:1,[PREFEAT:1,Sudden Strike],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sneak Attack]																													DESC:You have gone beyond the bounds of your monastic training to incorporate new modes of stealthy combat. Although your fellow monks may frown on your methods, none can doubt that your diverse training has improved your ability to strike precisely and bring down your foes quickly.																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|SneakAttackLvl|("CL=Monk")																						SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:When you use an unarmed strike with a sneak attack to deliver a stunning attack, you add 2 to the DC of your stunning attempt. If you have levels in rogue and monk, those levels stack for the purpose of determining your unarmed strike damage.
Brachiation					TYPE:General.Scout																																																								PRESKILL:2,Climb=4,Jump=4																								DESC:You can swing through trees like a monkey.																																									MOVECLONE:Walk,Brachiation,*1																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:You can move through wooded areas at your base land speed, ignoring any effects on movement due to terrain. You must be at least 20 feet from the ground to use this ability. This ability works only in medium and dense forests
Brutal Throw				TYPE:General.Fighter																																																																																				DESC:You have learned how to hurl weapons to deadly effect.																																																	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.THROWN|STR-DEX																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:You can add your Strength modifier (instead of your Dexterity modifier) to attack rolls with thrown weapons.
Combat Intuition				TYPE:General.Fighter																PREATT:5																																							PRESKILL:1,Sense Motive=4																								DESC:Your keen understanding of your opponent's moves and your instinctive feel for the flow of combat enable you to shrewdly assess your opponent's combat capabilities.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:As a free action, you can use Sense Motive to assess the challenge presented by a single opponent in relationship to your own level/Hit Dice (see the assess opponent option under the Sense Motive skill, page 102). You gain a +4 bonus on such checks and narrow the result to a single category. In addition, whenever you make a melee attack against a creature that you made a melee attack against during the previous round, you gain a +1 insight bonus on your melee attack rolls against that creature.
Danger Sense				TYPE:General.Scout																											PREFEAT:1,Improved Initiative																																																					DESC:You are one twitchy individual.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:Once per day, you can reroll an initiative check you have just made. You use the better of your two rolls. You must decide to reroll before the round starts.
Death Blow					TYPE:General																	PREATT:2										PREFEAT:1,Improved Initiative																																																					DESC:You waste no time in dealing with downed foes.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:You can perform a coup de grace attack against a helpless defender as a standard action. Doing this still provokes attacks of opportunity as normal.
Deft Opportunist				TYPE:General																												PREFEAT:1,Combat Reflexes																																											PRESTAT:1,DEX=15								DESC:You are prepared for the unexpected.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:You get a +4 bonus on attack rolls when making attacks of opportunity.
Deft Strike					TYPE:General																												PREFEAT:1,Combat Expertise										PREMULT:1,[PREFEAT:1,Sudden Strike],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sneak Attack]	PRESKILL:1,Spot=10															PRESTAT:1,DEX=13								DESC:You can place attacks at weak points in your opponent's defenses.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.106	BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can attempt to find a weak point in a visible target's armor. This requires a Spot check against a DC equal to your target's Armor Class. If you succeed, your next attack against that target (which must be made no later than your next turn) ignores the target's armor bonus and natural armor bonus to AC (including any enhancement bonuses to armor or natural armor). Other AC bonuses still apply normally.
Devoted Inquisitor			TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Smite Evil																													PREMULT:1,[PREFEAT:1,Sudden Strike],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sneak Attack]																													DESC:Your faithful service to your patron deity involves training and methods that many paladins consider questionable. By using the unconventional methods of rogues and assassins, you have learned to deliver devastating sneak attacks against evil foes.																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.107	BENEFIT:When you successfully use your sneak attack ability and your smite evil ability against the same foe in a single attack, you can potentially daze your foe. An opponent affected by both abilities must make a Will saving throw (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Cha modifier) or be dazed for 1 round.
Devoted Performer				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bardic Music,Smite Evil																																																																						DESC:You have foregone the pursuit of frivolous musical talents, instead entering religious training in service of honor and justice.																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|SmiteEvilDamageLvl|var("CL=Bard")	BONUS:VAR|BardicMusicTimes|var("CL=Paladin")													SOURCEPAGE:p.107	BENEFIT:If you have levels in paladin and bard, those levels stack for the purpose of determining the bonus damage dealt by your smite evil ability and determining the number of times per day that you can use your bardic music. This feat does not allow additional daily uses of smite evil or bardic music abilities beyond what your class levels would normally allow.
Devoted Tracker				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Smite Evil,Wild Empathy													PREFEAT:1,Track																																																DEFINE:SpecialMountAnimalCompanionLvl|0	DESC:You have found a balance between your woodland training and your devotion to religious training, blending these two aspects into one seamless whole.																																																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|WildEmpathy|var("CL=Paladin")	BONUS:VAR|SmiteEvilDamageLvl|var("CL=Ranger")	BONUS:VAR|SpecialMountAnimalCompanionLvl|SpecialMountLvl+AnimalCompanionLvl	SOURCEPAGE:p.108	BENEFIT:If you have levels in paladin and ranger, those levels stack for the purposes of determining the extra damage dealt by your smite evil ability and determining the bonus for your wild empathy class feature. This feat does not allow additional daily uses of smite evil. If you have both the special mount and animal companion class features, you can designate your special mount as your animal companion. The mount gains all the benefits of being both your special mount and your animal companion.
Disguise Spell				TYPE:General																												PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bardic Music																										PRESKILL:1,TYPE.Perform=9																								DESC:You can cast spells without observers noticing.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.108	BENEFIT:You can cast spells unobtrusively, mingling verbal and somatic components into your performances.
Dive for Cover				TYPE:General																			PRECHECKBASE:1,Reflex=4																																																															DESC:You can dive behind cover or drop to the ground quickly enough to avoid many area effects.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.108	BENEFIT:If you fail a Reflex saving throw, you can immediately attempt the saving throw again. You must take the second result, whether it succeeds or fails. You become prone immediately after attempting the second roll.
Dual Strike					TYPE:General.Fighter																											PREFEAT:2,Two Weapon Fighting,Improved Two Weapon Fighting																																																DESC:You are an expert skirmisher skilled at fighting with two weapons. Your extensive training with two weapons allows you to attack with both while moving through a chaotic combat or fighting a running battle.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.108	BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can make a melee attack with your primary weapon and your off-hand weapon. Both attacks use the same attack roll to determine success, using the worse of the two weapons' attack modifiers. If you are using a one-handed or light weapon in your primary hand and a light weapon in your off hand, you take a -4 penalty on this attack roll; otherwise you take a -10 penalty.
Expert Tactician				TYPE:General																	PREATT:2										PREFEAT:1,Combat Reflexes																																											PRESTAT:1,DEX=13								DESC:Your tactical skills work to your advantage.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.109	BENEFIT:If you hit a creature with an attack of opportunity, you and all your allies gain a +2 circumstance bonus on melee attack rolls and damage rolls against that creature for 1 round.
Extra Music					TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bardic Music																																																																								DESC:You can use your bardic music more often than you otherwise could.																																					STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE																																																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:VAR|BardicMusicTimes|4																								SOURCEPAGE:p.109	BENEFIT:You can use your bardic music four extra times per day.
Extraordinary Concentration		TYPE:General																																																									PRESKILL:1,Concentration=15																								DESC:Your mind is so focused that you can cast spells even while concentrating on another spell.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.109	BENEFIT:When concentrating to maintain a spell, you can make a Concentration check (DC 25 + spell level) to maintain concentration with just a move action. If you beat the DC by 10 or more, you can maintain concentration on the spell as a swift action
Extraordinary Spell Aim			TYPE:General																																																									PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=15																								DESC:You can shape a spell's area to exclude one creature from its effects.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.109	BENEFIT:Whenever you cast a spell with an area, you can attempt to shape the spell's area so that one creature within the area is unaffected by the spell. To accomplish this, you must succeed on a Spellcraft check (DC 25 + spell level).
Force of Personality			TYPE:General																																																																											PRESTAT:1,CHA=13								DESC:You have cultivated an unshakable belief in your self worth. Your sense of self and purpose are so strong that they bolster your willpower.																													BONUS:CHECKS|Will|CHA-WIS																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.109	BENEFIT:You add your Charisma modifier (instead of your Wisdom modifier) to Will saves against mind-affecting spells and abilities.																																																																																																			TEMPDESC:Bonus against Mind-Affecting effects.
Goad						TYPE:General.Fighter																PREATT:1																																																									PRESTAT:1,CHA=13								DESC:You are skilled at inducing opponents to attack you.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.109	BENEFIT:As a move action, you can goad an opponent that threatens you, has line of sight to you, can hear you, and has an Intelligence of 3 or higher. (The goad is a mind-affecting ability.) When the goaded opponent starts its next turn, if it threatens you and has line of sight to you, it must make a Will saving throw (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Cha modifier). If the opponent fails its save, you are the only creature it can make melee attacks against during this turn.
Green Ear					TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bardic Music																																												PRESKILL:1,TYPE.Perform=10																								DESC:Your bardic music can affect plant creatures.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:You can alter any of your mind-affecting bardic music abilities (or similar Perform-based abilities from other classes) so that they influence only plant creatures instead of other creatures. However, plants receive a +5 bonus on Will saves against any of these effects.
Hear the Unseen				TYPE:General.Scout																											PREFEAT:1,Blind Fight																										PRESKILL:1,Listen=5																									DESC:Your sense of hearing is so acute that you can partially pinpoint an opponent's location by sound, allowing you to strike even if the opponent is concealed or displaced.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:As a move action that does not provoke attacks of opportunity, you can attempt a DC 25 Listen check. If successful, you can pinpoint the location of all foes within 30 feet, as long as you have line of effect to them. This benefit does not eliminate the normal miss chance for fighting foes with concealment, but it ensures that you can target the correct square with your attacks.
Improved Diversion			TYPE:General.Fighter																																																								PRESKILL:1,Bluff=4																									DESC:You can create a diversion to hide quickly and with less effort.																																																					BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|4|PREAPPLY:PC																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:You can use Bluff to create a diversion to hide as a move action. You gain a +4 bonus on Bluff checks made for this purpose.																																																																																																		TEMPDESC:Bonus to create a diversion.
Improved Flight				TYPE:General																																						PREMOVE:1,Fly=1																																													DESC:You gain greater maneuverability when flying than you would normally have.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:Your maneuverability class while flying improves by one step-clumsy to poor, poor to average, average to good, or good to perfect.
Improved Swimming				TYPE:General.Scout.Exemplar																																																							PRESKILL:1,Swim=6																										DESC:You can swim faster than you normally could.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:You can swim half your speed as a move action or your speed as a full-round action.
Insightful Reflexes			TYPE:General																																																																																					DESC:Your keen intellect allows you an uncanny knack for evading dangerous effects.																																								BONUS:CHECKS|Reflex|INT-DEX																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:You add your Intelligence modifier (instead of your Dexterity modifier) to Reflex saves.
Jack of All Trades			TYPE:General																																																																											PRESTAT:1,INT=13								DESC:You have picked up a smattering of even the most obscure skills.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:You can use any skill as if you had 1/2 rank in that skill. This benefit allows you to attempt checks with skills that normally don't allow untrained skill checks (such as Decipher Script and Knowledge). If a skill doesn't allow skill checks (such as Speak Language), this feat has no effect.
Leap Attack					TYPE:General																												PREFEAT:1,Power Attack																										PRESKILL:1,Jump=8																										DESC:You can combine a powerful charge and a mighty leap into one devastating attack.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.110	BENEFIT:You can combine a jump with a charge against an opponent. If you cover at least 10 feet of horizontal distance with your jump, and you end your jump in a square from which you threaten your target, you can double the extra damage dealt by your use of the Power Attack feat. If you use this tactic with a two-handed weapon, you instead triple the extra damage from Power Attack.
Lingering Song				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bardic Music																																																																								DESC:Your inspirational bardic music stays with the listeners long after the last note has died away.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:If you use bardic music to inspire courage, inspire greatness, or inspire heroics, the effect lasts for 1 minute after an inspired ally stops hearing you play.
Mobile Spellcasting			TYPE:General																																																									PRESKILL:1,Concentration=8																								DESC:Your focused concentration allows you to move while casting a spell.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:You can make a special Concentration check (DC 20 + spell level) when casting a spell. If the check succeeds, you can cast the spell and move up to your speed as a single standard action.
Natural Bond				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Animal Companion																																																																							DESC:Your bond with your animal companion is exceptionally strong.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	BONUS:VAR|AnimalCompanionLvl|min(var("TL")-var("AnimalCompanionLvl"),3)																	SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:Add three to your effective druid level for the purpose of determining the bonus Hit Dice, extra tricks, special abilities, and other bonuses that your animal companion receives (see page 36 of the Player's Handbook). This bonus can never make your effective druid level exceed your character level.
Obscure Lore				TYPE:General					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Loremaster Lore,Bardic Knowledge																																																																					DESC:You are a treasure trove of little-known information.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|BardicKnowledge|4|TYPE=Insight	BONUS:VAR|SecretLore|4|TYPE=Insight																SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:You gain a +4 insight bonus on checks using your bardic knowledge or lore class feature.
Open Minded					TYPE:General.Exemplar																																																																																				DESC:You are naturally able to reroute your memory and skill expertise.																																					STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE																																																																																																												BONUS:SKILLPOOL|NUMBER|5																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:You immediately gain 5 skill points. Spend these skill points as normal. You cannot exceed the normal maximum ranks for your level in any skill.
Oversized Two Weapon Fighting		TYPE:General.Fighter																											PREFEAT:1,Two Weapon Fighting																																											PRESTAT:1,STR=13								DESC:You are adept at wielding larger than normal weapons in your off hand.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:When wielding a one-handed weapon in your off hand, you take penalties for fighting with two weapons as if you were wielding a light weapon in your off hand.
Power Throw					TYPE:General.Fighter																											PREFEAT:2,Brutal Throw,Power Attack																																										PRESTAT:1,STR=13								DESC:You have learned how to hurl weapons to deadly effect.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.111	BENEFIT:On your turn, before making any attack rolls, you can choose to subtract a number from all thrown weapon attack rolls and add the same number to all thrown weapon damage rolls. This number may not exceed your base attack bonus. The penalty on attack rolls and the bonus on damage rolls applies until your next turn.
Quick Reconnoiter				TYPE:General.Scout																																																								PRESKILL:2,Listen=5,Spot=5																								DESC:You can learn a lot of information from just a quick scan of an area or object.																																												BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|2																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.112	BENEFIT:You can make one Spot check and one Listen check each round as a free action. You also gain a +2 bonus on initiative checks.
Razing Strike				TYPE:General																							PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=5															PREMULT:1,[PREFEAT:1,Sudden Strike],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sneak Attack]																													DESC:You have mastered the art of delivering precise strikes against nonliving creatures while channeling spell energy through your melee attacks.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.112	BENEFIT:To activate this feat, you must sacrifice one of your daily allotment of spells (minimum spell level 1st). Doing this is a swift action that doesn't provoke attacks of opportunity. In exchange, you gain an insight bonus on your melee attack rolls and damage rolls for 1 round. The bonus on attack rolls equals the level of the spell sacrificed. The bonus on damage rolls is 1d6 points per level of the spell sacrificed, plus any extra damage based on your sneak attack ability. These bonuses apply against only one type of creature, depending on the type of spell sacrificed. If you sacrifice an arcane spell, they apply against constructs; if the sacrificed spell is divine, the bonuses apply against undead.
